1. Create Vnet, 1 public subnet, 1 private subnet, 1 for Application gateway subnet, 1 basionhost ,1 private vm, create nat and attach to private subnet

2. Connect the private server via bation-host and run command --> sudo apt upadate -y --> sudo apt install apache2 -y  --> systemctl start apache2 --> systemctl enable apache2

3. use this project for deployment https://github.com/Gaurav-kangane/Pathbased-routing-project.git

4. copy the monolithic index.html file in private server --> vi /var/www/html/index.html  --> systemctl restart apache2

5. Search Application Gateway and create create 1 subnet with outbound access choose that subnet while creating 

6. Go to frontends choose ip address type public and add new ipv4 address then go to backends

7. add backend pool --> give name and choose the private vm and save go next

8. Click Add routing rule --> give name, priority = 100, click on backend targets, choose backend target and backend setting add new give name keep as it is then save

9. Create separate 3 private server for aws, azure, gcp and paste index.html in /var/www/html/index.html then click on --> Add multiple targets to create a path-based rule
   give path /aws --> target name --> and choose backend seeting --> backend target give aws server same do it for azure and gcp

10. Click next till review and create, after successfully create then go applcaiton gateways click on your gateways copy pubilc ip and search on internet check application working or not. 

11. Go and search DNS Zones (it is like route53 in aws ) --> create, Name = gkangane.shop (your domain name), and create it.

12. Go to godaddy website login account click on profile click on your products --> Domain --> click on DNS --> click on Nameserver --> change Nameservers

13. Copy all the name server don't copy dot and paste on the godaddy nameserver.

14. In dns zones click on record sets --> click Add --> type A --> alias --> yes --> click on Azure resource and choose Application gateway ip --> Add

15. check gkangane.shop 
